        content: 'The Company will not discriminate against a User that chooses to exercise any rights related to a User\'s privacy or Personal Information. The Company will not deny goods or services, charge different prices or rates, provide a different level of service or quality of goods, or suggest that a User might receive a different price or level of quality for goods as a result of User exercising any rights herein.\n\nColorado, Connecticut, Delaware, Iowa, Montana, Nebraska, New Hampshire, Oregon, Tennessee, Texas, Utah, and Virginia\n\nThese additional rights and disclosures may apply to residents of Colorado, Connecticut, Delaware, Iowa, Montana, Nebraska, New Hampshire, Oregon, Tennessee, Texas, Utah, and Virginia.\n\nData Subject Requests\n\nIf a User is a resident of these states, these state\'s law may provide some or all of the following rights:\n\nTo confirm whether or not the Company is processing User\'s personal data;\nTo access User\'s personal data;\nTo correct inaccuracies in User\'s personal data;\nTo delete User\'s personal data;\nTo obtain a copy of User\'s personal data that User previously provided to the Company in a portable and readily usable format; or\nTo obtain a list of third parties to which the Company disclosed User\'s personal data.\n\nTo exercise any of these rights, a User must submit a request as provided for in Article 12. Please note these rights are subject to exceptions. If a User has an account with the Company, the Company may require User to use the account to submit the request. In the request, please specify which right User is seeking to exercise and the scope of the request. The Company will confirm receipt of the request within 10 days and respond to the request within 45 days. To verify User identity, the Company may require a User to confirm receipt of an email sent to an email address that matches Company records, provide the Company with details relating to User\'s history with the Company, or provide additional information. If the Company is unable to verify a User\'s identity, the Company may deny User\'s request.\n\nSales and Targeted Advertising\n\nThe Company does not disclose or otherwise sell personal data (e.g., identifiers and service and platform usage) or Personal Information to any third party for the purposes of selling such personal data or Personal Information or for providing targeted or behavioral advertising.\n\nProfiling\n\nThe Company does not process personal data or Personal Information for purposes of profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects concerning consumers.\n\nDesignated Methods and Authorized Agents\n\nAll rights requests must be exercised through the designated methods listed above. A User may make a rights request using an authorized agent. The Company requires written and signed proof of the agent\'s permission to do so and the Company may verify User identity directly with the User.\n\nAppeal\n\nA User may have the right to appeal the Company\'s denial of User\'s request. To appeal, please contact the Company at the email address provided in Article 12 and specify what the User would like to appeal. The Company will review and respond to the appeal in accordance with applicable law. If the Company denies the appeal, the User may submit a complaint as follows:\n\nFor Colorado residents, visit https://coag.gov/file-complaint/\nFor Connecticut residents, visit https://www.dir.ct.gov/ag/complaint/\nFor Delaware residents, visit https://attorneygeneral.delaware.gov/fraud/cmu/complaint/\nFor Iowa residents, visit https://www.iowaattorneygeneral.gov/for-consumers/file-a-consumer-complaint\nFor Montana residents, visit https://dojmt.gov/office-of-consumer-protection/consumer-complaints/\nFor Nebraska residents, visit https://www.nebraska.gov/apps-ago-complaints/\nFor New Hampshire residents, visit https://www.doj.nh.gov/citizens/consumer-protection-antitrust-bureau/consumer-complaints\nFor Oregon residents, visit https://www.doj.state.or.us/oregon-department-of-justice/contact-us/\nFor Tennessee residents, visit https://www.tn.gov/attorneygeneral/working-for-tennessee/consumer/file-a-complaint\nFor Texas residents, visit https://www.texasattorneygeneral.gov/consumer-protection/file-consumer-complaint\nFor Utah residents, visit https://attorneygeneral.utah.gov/contact/complaint-form/\nFor Virginia residents, visit https://www.oag.state.va.us/consumercomplaintform\n\n[Canada] Under PIPEDA, you may request access to and correction of your personal information. If you are not satisfied with our response, you may contact the Office of the Privacy Commissioner of Canada. To exercise your rights, email info@knowhere.co.jp.\n\n[República Dominicana] Conforme a la Ley 172‑13, usted puede ejercer los derechos de acceso, rectificación, cancelación y oposición respecto de sus datos personales. Sus datos pueden transferirse y alojarse en [United States and Japan]. Para ejercer sus derechos: info@knowhere.co.jp.\n\n[Panamá] De acuerdo con la Ley 81/2019 y su Decreto 285/2021, usted puede solicitar acceso, rectificación, cancelación u oposición de sus datos. Podemos transferir y almacenar datos en [United States and Japan]. Solicitudes: info@knowhere.co.jp.\n\n[Nicaragua] Bajo la Ley 787, usted puede ejercer derechos de acceso, rectificación, oposición y cancelación sobre sus datos personales. Los datos pueden transferirse a y almacenarse en [United States and Japan]. Contacto: info@knowhere.co.jp.\n\n[Venezuela] Respetamos los derechos de acceso, rectificación y eliminación reconocidos por la normativa aplicable. Sus datos pueden alojarse en [United States and Japan]. Para solicitudes: info@knowhere.co.jp.\n\n[대한민국] 만 14세 미만 사용자의 개인정보 처리는 법정대리인의 동의를 전제로 합니다. 귀하는 개인정보의 열람·정정·삭제·처리정지 등을 요청할 수 있습니다. 서비스 제공을 위해 개인정보가 [United States and Japan]의 서버로 이전·보관될 수 있습니다. 문의: info@knowhere.co.jp\n\n[台灣] 您依據《個人資料保護法》就本服務所蒐集、處理或利用之個人資料,得行使查詢、請求閱覽或製給複製本、補充或更正、請求停止蒐集/處理/利用,以及請求刪除之權利。資料可能傳輸並保存於 [United States and Japan] 之伺服器。如欲行使權利,請聯絡 info@knowhere.co.jp。'
      }
    ]
  }
};

function PageInner() {
  const router = useRouter();
  const [currentLang, setCurrentLang] = useState<'ja' | 'en'>('en');

  useEffect(() => {
    // クエリパラメータから言語を取得
    const lang = router.query.lang as string;
    if (lang === 'ja' || lang === 'en') {
      setCurrentLang(lang);
    }
  }, [router.query.lang]);

  const handleLanguageChange = (lang: 'ja' | 'en') => {
    setCurrentLang(lang);
    // URLのクエリパラメータも更新
    router.push(`/privacy-policy?lang=${lang}`, undefined, { shallow: true });
  };

  const content = privacyPolicyContent[currentLang];

  return (
    <Box
      sx={{
        px: { xs: 2, sm: 4, md: 6 },
        py: 2,
      }}
    >
      <Box sx={{
        display: 'flex',
        flexDirection: { xs: 'column', sm: 'row' },
        justifyContent: 'space-between',
        alignItems: { xs: 'flex-start', sm: 'center' },
        gap: { xs: 2, sm: 0 },
        mb: 3
      }}>
        <Typography variant="h2" sx={{
          fontSize: { xs: '1.75rem', sm: '2rem', md: '2.25rem' }
        }}>
          {content.title}
        </Typography>
        <Stack direction="row" spacing={1}>
          <Button
            variant={currentLang === 'en' ? 'contained' : 'outlined'}
            onClick={() => handleLanguageChange('en')}
            size="small"
          >
            English
          </Button>
          <Button
            variant={currentLang === 'ja' ? 'contained' : 'outlined'}
            onClick={() => handleLanguageChange('ja')}
            size="small"
          >
            日本語
          </Button>
        </Stack>
      </Box>
      <Stack direction="column" justifyContent="center" spacing={3}>
        {content.sections.map((section, index) => (
          <Box key={index}>
            <Typography variant="h6" sx={{
              mb: 1,
              fontWeight: 'bold',
              fontSize: { xs: '1.1rem', sm: '1.25rem' }
            }}>
              {section.title}
            </Typography>
            <Typography sx={{
              whiteSpace: 'pre-wrap',
              fontSize: { xs: '0.875rem', sm: '1rem' },
              lineHeight: { xs: 1.5, sm: 1.6 }
            }}>
              {section.content}
            </Typography>
          </Box>
        ))}
      </Stack>
    </Box>
  );
}

export default function Page() {
  return <PageInner />;
}

Page.getLayout = function getLayout(page: ReactElement) {
  return <DocumentsLayout tab="privacy">{page}</DocumentsLayout>;
};

